title: AHS: DOUBLE FEATURE Episode 3 Breakdown, Theories, and Details You Missed!
author: Think Story
comment:
What did we think of Episode 3 THIRST?

Check out my episode 1 & 2 breakdown here: https://youtu.be/AbOBLHPTgUI
Mickey’s face when Ursula was mean to him at the bar made me feel so badly for him. I wanted to hug him. I like his character and I hope he is in every episode
I surprisingly enjoy Leslie this season. Ursula is gonna get all her ways for sure, so not worried about her ...
Plot twist, Ryan Murphy took the pill to write this season and that’s why it’s good

This episode made me uncomfortable, and that’s what true horror is to me. This was definitely one of the best AHS episodes in a VERY long time. Stories isn’t even at the level of this new season of AHS. I just think it’s weird that Doris doesn’t seem to be weirded out by the fact Harry sucked her blood from her finger cut, and Alma was literally eating a rabbit. She was worried more about what she might have caught, instead of the fact that her child was eating an animal. Little stuff like that is off, but overall, I’m into this season.
